{"image_id": "KEY_2015_page_107", "image_size": [1275, 1650], "ocr": [{"text": "Net loan charge-offs", "bbox": [162.5, 159.1, 333.8, 179.9]}, {"text": "Net loan charge-offs for 2015 totaled $142 million, or .24% of average loans, compared to net loan charge-offs of", "bbox": [162.5, 209.1, 1112.5, 229.9]}, {"text": "$113 million, or .20%, for the same period last year. Figure 39 shows the trend in our net loan charge-offs by", "bbox": [162.5, 234.1, 1073.6, 254.9]}, {"text": "loan type, while the composition of loan charge-offs and recoveries by type of loan is presented in Figure 40.", "bbox": [162.5, 259.1, 1073.7, 279.9]}, {"text": "Over the past 12 months, net loan charge-offs increased $29 million. This increase is attributable to the growth in", "bbox": [162.5, 309.1, 1108.6, 329.9]}, {"text": "our loan portfolio and lower levels of recoveries over the same period. As shown in Figure 42, our exit loan", "bbox": [162.5, 334.1, 1061.3, 354.9]}, {"text": "portfolio contributed a total of $10 million in net loan charge-offs for 2015, compared to $13 million in net loan", "bbox": [162.5, 359.1, 1097.1, 379.9]}, {"text": "charge-offs for 2014. The decrease in net loan charge-offs in our exit loan portfolio was primarily driven by", "bbox": [162.5, 384.1, 1063.3, 404.9]}, {"text": "lower levels of net loan charge-offs in our consumer and commercial exit loan portfolios.", "bbox": [162.5, 409.1, 907.9, 429.9]}, {"text": "Figure 39. Net Loan Charge-offs from Continuing Operations (a)", "bbox": [353.4, 458.9, 921.6, 479.7]}, {"text": "Year ended December 31,", "bbox": [162.5, 505.1, 311.7, 518.7]}, {"text": "dollars in millions", "bbox": [162.5, 520.7, 262.0, 534.3]}, {"text": "2015", "bbox": [772.1, 520.7, 799.2, 534.3]}, {"text": "2014", "bbox": [850.4, 520.7, 877.5, 534.3]}, {"text": "2013", "bbox": [928.8, 520.7, 955.8, 534.3]}, {"text": "2012", "bbox": [1007.1, 520.7, 1034.2, 534.3]}, {"text": "2011", "bbox": [1085.4, 520.7, 1112.5, 534.3]}, {"text": "Commercial, f